             /CONDITIONAL CALL AND SET FLAG. THE 1ST WORD FOLLOWING THE JMS IS AN
             /OFFSET INTO THE BUFFER. THE TWO WORDS AT THAT OFFSET, C AND S, DEFINE
             /A SECTOR, WITH C AT THE CENTER AND S THE DISTANCE FROM THE CENTER TO T
             /AN EDGE. R4 IS A FLAG. IF IT IS NOT ZERO ON ENTRY, RETURN. IF NOT
             /COMPARE THE VALUE IN THE AC TO THE SECTOR. IF IT IS WITHIN THE SECTOR,
             /CALL EITHER THE SSR, RSR, OR SMR DEPENDING ON THE 2ND WORD FOLLOWING

